22/09/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Skopje hosted a round table discussion Friday (19 September) on asylum and refugees. Participants in the event, which was organised by the government and the UN High Commissioner for Refugees, agreed that asylum is a priority of Macedonia's Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU and said local legislation should comply with EU policy and standards on asylum and protection of refugees. Earlier, the European Commission granted Macedonia 2m euros through the CARDS programme to develop a national plan on migration and asylum. (MIA, Makfax - 19/09/03)
